<p><b>Durango</b> is a city in <a href="/wiki/Dubuque_County,_Iowa" title="Dubuque County, Iowa">Dubuque County</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iowa" title="Iowa">Iowa</a>, <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>. It is part of the <a href="/wiki/Dubuque,_Iowa" title="Dubuque, Iowa">Dubuque, Iowa</a> <a href="/wiki/Metropolitan_Statistical_Area" title="Metropolitan Statistical Area" class="mw-redirect">Metropolitan Statistical Area</a>. The population was 22 at the 2010 census, down from 24 at the 2000 census.</p>

<p>Durango is located at <span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion"><a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Durango%2C_Iowa&amp;params=42_33_36_N_90_46_33_W_type:city"><span class="geo-default"><span class="geo-dms" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location"><span class="latitude">42°„33°‰36°ÂN</span> <span class="longitude">90°„46°‰33°ÂW</span></span></span><span class="geo-multi-punct">? / ?</span><span class="geo-nondefault"><span class="geo-dec" title="Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location">42.56000°„N 90.77583°„W</span><span style="display:none">? / <span class="geo">42.56000; -90.77583</span></span></span></a></span> (42.560063, -90.775907).<sup id="cite_ref-GR1_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GR1-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="2010_census">2010 census</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Durango,_Iowa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: 2010 census">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>As of the <a href="/wiki/Census" title="Census">census</a><sup id="cite_ref-FactFinder_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FactFinder-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> of 2010, there were 22 people, 10 households, and 6 families residing in the city. The <a href="/wiki/Population_density" title="Population density">population density</a> was 550.0 inhabitants per square mile (212.4&#160;/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 10 housing units at an average density of 250.0 per square mile (96.5&#160;/km<sup>2</sup>). The racial makeup of the city was 100.0% <a href="/wiki/White_(U.S._Census)" title="White (U.S. Census)" class="mw-redirect">White</a>.</p>
<p>There were 10 households of which 20.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 60.0% were <a href="/wiki/Marriage" title="Marriage">married couples</a> living together, and 40.0% were non-families. 40.0% of all households were made up of individuals and 20% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.20 and the average family size was 3.00.</p>
<p>The median age in the city was 46 years. 18.2% of residents were under the age of 18; 13.5% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 13.5% were from 25 to 44; 27.2% were from 45 to 64; and 27.3% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the city was 63.6% male and 36.4% female.</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="2000_census">2000 census</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Durango,_Iowa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: 2000 census">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>As of the <a href="/wiki/Census" title="Census">census</a><sup id="cite_ref-GR2_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GR2-5"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup> of 2000, there were 24 people, 11 households, and 7 families residing in the city. The <a href="/wiki/Population_density" title="Population density">population density</a> was 709.8 people per square mile (308.9/km2). There were 12 housing units at an average density of 354.9 per square mile (154.4/km2). The racial makeup of the city was 100.00% <a href="/wiki/White_(U.S._Census)" title="White (U.S. Census)" class="mw-redirect">White</a>.</p>
<p>There were 11 households out of which 36.4% (4) have children under the age of 18 living with them, 45.5% (5) are <a href="/wiki/Marriage" title="Marriage">married couples</a> living together, 27.3% (3) have a female householder with no husband present, and 27.3% (3) are non-families. 27.3% (3) of all households are made up of individuals and 18.2% (2) have someone living alone who is 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.18 and the average family size was 2.50.</p>
<p>In the city the population was spread out with 20.8% (5) under the age of 18, 8.3% (2) from 18 to 24, 33.3% (8) from 25 to 44, 20.8% (5) from 45 to 64, and 16.7% (4) who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females there were 71.4 males (There are 14 females and 10 males). For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 72.7 males (That makes 10 females and 7 males).</p>
<p>The median income for a household in the city was $32,188, and the median income for a family was $55,625. Males had a median income of $0 versus $22,083 for females. The <a href="/wiki/Per_capita_income" title="Per capita income">per capita income</a> for the city was $19,827. There are 22.2% of families living below the <a href="/wiki/Poverty_line" title="Poverty line" class="mw-redirect">poverty line</a> and 15.4% of the population, including 50.0% of under eighteens and none of those over 64.</p>
